snippet.title: Buc-ee’s, My American Dream - Barron Trump Sings
snippet.description:
Buc-ee’s, My American Dream

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics

[Verse 1]
Woke up early, sun shining bright
Hit the road, under that red, white, and blue light
Cruisin’ down I-10, rollin’ clean and free
Had a craving for the heart of the land—Buc-ee’s was callin’ me

[Chorus]
Oh Buc-ee’s, you're the soul of the highway
With your brisket hot and your shelves stacked my way
It’s where the simple folk stop, and I stand in the line
With ranchers and dreamers and freedom on their mind
It ain't just a station, it's a patriotic theme
Buc-ee’s, my American dream

[Verse 2]
Walked through those doors, felt the AC kiss
Grabbed a beaver nugget bag—I was born for this
Cleanest restrooms in the land, God bless that shine
Even presidents should stop here sometime

[Chorus]
Oh Buc-ee’s, you're the heart of the nation
Beef jerky heaven, no need for translation
From cowboys to moms with the kids in the back
We all find a little peace in this roadside shack
It ain't just a pit stop, it’s stars and stripes supreme
Buc-ee’s, my American dream

[Bridge]
You don’t need a suit, or a name with a crown
Just love for your country and a tank runnin’ down
From Texas to Georgia, the beaver’s alive
It's where the humble and the hopeful arrive

[Chorus – Final]
Oh Buc-ee’s, wave that banner so bold
With your fudge and your T-shirts and your stories told
To every trucker and teen, to each family of five
You're a beacon of freedom where America thrives
More than a gas stop, more than a theme
Buc-ee’s, my American dream

[Outro – Spoken]
Yeah, I’ve been to palaces and marble halls…
But give me Buc-ee’s, and I’ve got it all.
